## Next Steps for User

To start collecting Speed Insights data:

1. **Enable Speed Insights in Vercel Dashboard**:
   - Navigate to your project on Vercel
   - Find "Speed Insights" in the sidebar
   - Click "Enable" to activate tracking routes

2. **Deploy to Vercel**:
   - Push this code to your connected Git repository, or
   - Run `vercel deploy` from the command line

3. **Monitor Performance**:
   - After deployment, visit your site to generate traffic
   - Check the Speed Insights dashboard within a few days to see performance metrics

## Technical Notes

- Speed Insights v2.0.0 includes the latest features and improvements
- The tracking script will be automatically injected at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` routes
- No additional configuration required for basic functionality
- Works on all Vercel plans (including free tier)
- Package manager: npm (using package-lock.json)

## Conclusion

No code changes were necessary. The project already has Vercel Speed Insights fully configured and ready to use. Simply enable it in your Vercel dashboard and deploy to start collecting performance data.
